The '''Junín-4 Oil Field''' is an [[oil field]] located in the [[Orinoco Belt]]. It was discovered in 2010 and developed by [[PDVSA]]. The oil field is operated and owned by [[PDVSA]]. The total [[proven reserves]] of the Junín-4 oil field are around {{convert|9|e9oilbbl}}, and production is centered on {{convert|350000|oilbbl/d|m3/d}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dundee.ac.uk/cepmlp/gateway/index.php?news=30930 |title=China's national oil companies build their presence in North and South America |year=2010 |publisher=dundee.ac.uk |accessdate=2014-04-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130804031728/http://www.dundee.ac.uk/cepmlp/gateway/index.php?news=30930 |archivedate=2013-08-04 |df= }}</ref>

